<TITLE> European shares turn positive, tracking US futures </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - European shares turned positive in early afternoon trading on Tuesday as US index futures strengthened. At 1125 GMT, the FTSEurofirst 300 index of top European shares was up 0.07 percent at 1,482.99 points, having spent the early part of the day in the red. Across the Atlantic, futures for the three major stock indexes were up between 0.1 and 0.2 percent. "The futures are turning around and some bank ADRs are being bid up," said a London-based trader. "As the days go by there's a feeling that the banking troubles may not be as bad as all that, and that the US may loosen monetary policy," he said. "A cut in the shadow rate may be a prelude to a 25 basis point cut in the Fed funds rate." Britain's FTSE 100 was flat while Germany's DAX and France's CAC 40 were up 0.4 perce
